a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes x :: real
assumes h0 : "x = 75"
shows  "cos (degrees x) = 0"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Compute $\cos 75^\circ.$ The final Answer is 0
 ### Proof
 From the angle addition formula, \begin{align} \cos 75^\circ &= \cos (45^\circ + 30^\circ) \\ &= \cos 45^\circ \cos 30^\circ - \sin 45^\circ \sin 30^\circ \\ &= \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} \cdot \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} - \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} \cdot \frac{1}{2} \\
 &= \boxed{\frac{\sqrt{6} - \sqrt{2}}{4}}. \end{align}
 *)

theorem
fixes x :: real
assumes h0 : "x = 75"
shows  "cos (degrees x) = 0"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
